&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Senior Sister - Band 7 Ocean Suite&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ocean Suite is a brand new facility providing a range of gynaecology, breast and pregnancy related in-patient services to Plymouth and the surrounding area.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the continued development of our service an exciting opportunity for a Band 7 Senior Sister has arisen.  This person will not only have proven leadership and management skills but will ideally have experience in gynaecology, breast, surgery and pregnancy related services.  Working closely with our outpatient and ambulatory departments an ability to review and transform pathways of care is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have current NMC registration, good management experience at Band 6 or 7 with proven ability to lead a team and develop nursing services.  With excellent organisational and communication skills they will also be required to manage a complex service while ensuring a gold standard of care for patients throughout their stay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a ward leader there will be an expectation of flexibility to respond to the needs of the service.  Specialist knowledge in women’s health is advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Hayley Foulkes (Senior Sister) on 01752 (4)32686 or Mrs Cath Williams (Matron) on 01752 (4)31789 or Bleep 0491.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are planned for w/c 16th November 2020.    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
